Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language generation in a conversational system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses how the system attempts to model informational novelty. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is relevant as the system uses corpus statistics to determine word order. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is possible as the paper describes the implementation of the NLG module in a prototype conversational system. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses how the system attempts to generate natural language that is appropriate for the given dialog state.
